This paper is about a platform for reinforcement learning research, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of parallel training and distributed computing, which could fall under categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also mentions the use of PyTorch, which is a popular deep learning framework, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the platform on Atari games, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
